    "name": "COU1: Total knee replacement tibial tray synovial flow (Class II)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of wear-particle transport and accumulation to variations in tibial tray geometry and gait-cycle loading for a Class II TKR device. Model influence is MEDIUM (bench-top tribological testing confirms relative ranking of designs); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect geometry decision could increase periprosthetic osteolysis risk). Model Risk Level 3.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case wear-particle accumulation zones across 6 gait-phase loading conditions for a Class II tibial tray. Results compared against µPIV experimental measurements using relative accumulation index (RAI < 1.15 acceptance criterion).",
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/cou/nagaraja-cou1-tkr-tibial/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "In-scope domain: cemented tibial tray, physiological gait loading, non-inflammatory synovial fluid",
      "description": "This COU applies exclusively to cemented tibial tray designs with a polyethylene insert operating under physiological gait-cycle loads (0.5–3.0 BW axial force) in non-inflammatory synovial fluid (viscosity 1–50 mPa·s). Metal-backed uncemented designs, rheumatoid arthritis fluid conditions, and impact loading exceeding 5 BW are explicitly out of scope."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/cou/nagaraja-cou1-tkr-tibial/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "Tibial tray CFD operating envelope — physiological gait bounds",
      "description": "Axial joint load: 0.5–3.0 × body weight (500–2100 N for 70 kg patient). Flexion angle: 0–120°. Synovial fluid dynamic viscosity: 1–50 mPa·s (shear-thinning Carreau model, n=0.6, λ=1.902 s). Wear particle diameter: 0.1–10 µm (UHMWPE). Tibial plateau area: 2200–3200 mm². Gait cycle frequency: 0.8–1.2 Hz. Fluid temperature: 37 ± 1 °C. Reynolds number at peak load: Re < 0.01 (creeping flow regime). All CFD predictions are valid only within these bounds; extrapolation to high-impact activities (running, jumping) is not supported."
    }
  },
