        "description": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to the non-Newtonian Carreau viscosity model in a 3D channel geometry. Observed order of convergence within 10% of theoretical second-order accuracy. Error norm < 0.1% at the production mesh resolution."
      },
      "rationale": "MMS verification performed on a 3D channel with Carreau shear-thinning fluid matching synovial fluid parameters. Spatial convergence study on 4 mesh levels (0.25M–8M cells) confirms OOC = 1.94 ± 0.08, consistent with second-order finite-volume discretization. Error at production mesh (2M cells): L2 norm 0.07%. Level 3 achieved."
    },
