        "name": "Discretization error Level 3 — GCI < 5% on QoI; Level 4 — GCI < 2%",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) computed on three systematically refined meshes using Richardson extrapolation. GCI on primary QoI (relative accumulation index) must be < 5% for Level 3 and < 2% for Level 4. Temporal convergence verified with Courant number < 0.5."
      },
      "rationale": "Three-mesh convergence study (0.8M, 2.0M, 5.1M cells; refinement ratio r=1.36) using GCI method per Celik et al. (2008). GCI_fine = 1.3% on RAI QoI. Temporal convergence confirmed at dt=0.001 s (CFL < 0.5). Achieved Level 4 exceeds MRL 3 requirement of Level 3."
