        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form Level 3 — physics selection justified with sensitivity analysis and literature support",
        "description": "The choice of governing equations (Navier-Stokes with Carreau viscosity model, Lagrangian particle tracking for wear debris) must be justified by literature precedent for synovial flow modeling and supported by a sensitivity analysis comparing alternative model forms (e.g., Newtonian vs. non-Newtonian, one-way vs. two-way coupling)."
      },
      "rationale": "Carreau non-Newtonian model selected based on Meng et al. (Tribology Int, 2020) and Askari & Andersen (J Biomech, 2021) demonstrating its superior accuracy for synovial fluid in TKR geometries. One-way Lagrangian coupling justified by particle volume fraction < 0.01% (dilute limit). Sensitivity analysis comparing Newtonian assumption shows 18% error in peak RAI, confirming non-Newtonian treatment is essential. Level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-mi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
