        "description": "All boundary conditions and material properties used in the COU simulations must be matched to the validation experiment inputs within documented tolerances. Differences exceeding 10% of the operating envelope range for any critical input must be justified with sensitivity analysis demonstrating negligible impact on QoI."
      },
      "rationale": "Systematic comparison of COU simulation inputs against validation experiment conditions performed for all 5 critical inputs. Maximum deviation: synovial viscosity 8% (15 mPa·s in validation vs. 14–16 mPa·s in COU range). Sensitivity analysis confirms 8% viscosity deviation produces < 2% change in RAI. All other inputs matched within 5% of operating envelope range. Equivalency documented in traceability matrix (EIP-TM-001). Level 3 achieved."
    }
